body:
> @junkaixue, you may have missed it, but for the past two months we have had a [helix-front specific PR template](https://github.com/apache/helix/blob/master/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/helix_front.md). This PR follows that template.

@helix-bot, Helix is Apache open source project. Any new proposal of development process change / template change requires approval from open source community. I dont believe you submit any request for that. Please follow current template before your new request submitted and approved.

For the old ones, it is what it is. But for non checked in PRs. Let's follow the standard. Otherwise, the PR is not allowed to merge.

@helix-bot . Firstly,  the new template usage is not something can be approved by any single committer or even single PMC. It should be agreed by a group of the Apache Helix PMC/Committer. Secondly, your contribution is highly appreciated but we need to respect the process.

At the same time, as your created a new workflow for helix-front CI. It never passed. We should stop this process of it: https://github.com/apache/helix/actions/workflows/helix-front.yml

This process can guarantee the quality of the delivery. I prefer not arguing on this. But the bottom line is following the template for any PR checkin. Thanks for the collaboration.

@helix-bot Thanks for the fix.
Please update the description and/or commit message when you have a chance, this PR does more things than its current title. Some local and CI test results in the "tests" section will be great.

Besides, IMHO this one is of high urgency because it blocks the whole project build and CI. We should resolve any conflicts and merge this ASAP.

@qqu0127 It looks like this `testClusterStatusMonitorLifecycle` is a known flaky test, with two to five previous failures documented in Github issues:

